                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 823.00/146</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 26, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have reliable information Leguistas have considered having him sworn in as
                    President and seek asylum at the Legation. Under such tactical move should it be
                    given? Conference failed to reach an understanding; proposals discussed include
                    resignation of both Leguia and Junta and general elections; negotiations
                    continue.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McMillin</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
